                <head>14. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 24, <persName corresp="#p_LW1">Wolf Ladejinsky</persName> wrote a
                    7-page letter to Walt <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName> covering the
                    political and economic situations in light of the Communist threat. He
                    concluded, “everything must be brought into play to insure the survival of
                    Vietnam.” (Kennedy Library, President’s Office File, Staff Memoranda, <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName>)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
